meowtrics (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Plasma 6 plasmoid fixes
    - Replace Plasma 5 toolTipMainText/SubText with Plasma 6 toolTipMainText
      properties at PlasmoidItem level (the old form errored at load).
    - Plasmoid icon: use the meowtrics logo (shipped at
      /usr/share/icons/hicolor/512x512/apps/meowtrics.png) instead of the
      generic face-smile system icon.
    - Wire Plasma5Support DataSource to actually call `meowtrics json`
      and update the popup sensor list every 5s.
  * Tray icon variation
    - Map (sensor, state) to a wider set of distinct freedesktop icon names
      (computer, system-run, memory, drive-harddisk, weather-clear,
      battery-good-charging, dialog-warning, ...) so the tray icon visibly
      changes between sensor states. True emoji rendering still planned for
      v0.2.
  * Packaging
    - Build .deb installs the logo to hicolor at 512x512.
    - postinst refreshes the icon cache and runs kbuildsycoca6 so the widget
      shows up in the chooser without re-login.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 19:00:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
    - Daemon that reads CPU and renders state through a tray emoji.
    - Foundation for the wider sensor lineup, KDE plasmoid frontend,
      and weighted message database.

